<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-07-03T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-07-03T12:00:00-05:00" n="615" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d615">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Italy)/6–3047:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Acting Political Adviser</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Greene</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">at
                                    Leghorn</hi><note n="1" xml:id="d615fn1">Mr. Greene was Acting
                                    United States Political Adviser to the Acting Supreme Allied
                                    Commander, Mediterranean Theater (Lee).</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-07-03T13:00:00-04:00">July
                                        3, 1947—1 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>55. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 115 June 30.<note n="2" xml:id="d615fn2">Not printed.</note>
                                <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> with State concurrence approved
                                Brit proposed reply <gloss target="#t_Naf1">Naf</gloss> 1342,<note n="3" xml:id="d615fn3">In this telegram, June 26, from Leghorn,
                                    not printed, <gloss target="#t_SACMED1">SACMED</gloss>
                                    recommended that <gloss target="#t_AFHQ1">AFHQ</gloss> continue
                                    to exercise command in the Mediterranean Theater until
                                    ratification by Yugoslavia of the treaty of peace with Italy
                                    (Defense files).</note> authorizing continuance <gloss target="#t_AFHQ1">AFHQ</gloss> during period (if any) between
                                    <gloss target="#t_RDay1">R</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_RJ1">RJ</gloss> days with proviso <gloss target="#t_AFHQ1">AFHQ</gloss> functions vis-à-vis Itals terminate <gloss target="#t_RDay1">R day</gloss>.</p>
                            <p>You shd stress to Gen Lee view this Govt Allied mil in Italy must
                                respect scrupulously restoration Ital sovereignty upon coming into
                                force treaty and abide strictly by that principle in interpretation
                                rights mil and civil affairs agreement.</p>
                            <p>Dept does not desire approach Yugos re their deposit
                                ratification.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>